reviews.text: Food quality in lunch sets is good. Price for lunch sets is acceptable, ranging from about $100 - $200. Good and efficient services from waiters/ waitresses.

Very nice japanese restaurant. Good service and didnt need to wait for long. 
Menu has sashimi/sushi/rolls, Teppayaki, yakimono, sukiyaki etc. Lots to choose from. 

We had the #1203 Assorted Sashimi and Sushi set, #505 Angus Beef rice (in hot pot) and some kind of cold noodles. The angus beef was very good and came with a small miso soup as well.
Pricey in terms of food quality, does not seem like authentic japanese food in general
Good value for the quality of food.
Delicious Japanese food, friendly service, and exceptional value for money.

reviews.text: Nice ambience. The reception told us that a minimum charge of HKD 1000 for a table when we has no reservation. It was not along the window side. Food was good. Service was alright but not great. The bar  has good view but was very crowded  though.

Very bad. Ordered crispy fish and after 20min of waiting they came to tell they don't have it. Ordered another type of fish and after 10min they told they don't have it either. Spring rolls were really oily and heavy, as was the soft shell crab. AND THEY CHARGED SEPARATELY FOR THE NUTS! Nice harbor view but everything else sucked. Too touristic!
Very warm, polite and caring staff. Very good food quality. Have a good view of the world famous Victoria Harbour.  I love this restaurant.
Great view. Food is ok. Connected to the eyebar.
Pricey for what it is but undeniably gorgeous views of the  Hong Kong habour. The service is alright too. There are some fun twists to dishes. We came here twice in the same week.

維港view，茶餐廳水準嘅服務

Excellent view, satisfactory food, poor service due to poor training......

同三個朋友食lunch，坦白講我極少嚟呢種餐廳食飯，去酒店餐廳就多少少經驗，但唔使同同級比較都知服務有幾差......

食物唔算大問題，預咗嚟食景，問題係啲侍應嘅質素，一坐低就sell你叫杯蔗汁羅漢果茶，但凍熱都落錯，幫你加茶時就有兩滴茶倒落碟餸度......

香港飲食業嘅通病

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
